article.headline: Mercer 92, Campbell 86
article.story: MACON, Ga. (AP) -- Delmar Wilson scored a career-high 26 points and added nine rebounds to lead Mercer to a 92-86 victory over Campbell on Saturday. Mercer (7-8, 4-2 Atlantic Sun Conference) overcame an early 10-point deficit to build a 23-point lead, only to see Campbell (0-12, 0-5) use six 3-point baskets in a 31-point explosion over the final seven minutes that cut the lead to 89-86 with eight seconds remaining. Anthony Atkinson led the Camels with 19 points and Derek Gray added a career-high 15. Campbell's Tarick Johnson, Dominque and Colin Hunt each added 10. Wesley Duke added 17 for the Bears and Jay January 16 as Mercer extended its home court winning streak to 13 games.
